<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Does the layout reflow on small screens?

No — tiles use absolute pixel coordinates, so a free-form dashboard does not //reflow// to narrow viewports (that is inherent to the free-form model). Instead, turn on ''Fit to screen'' (the toolbar toggle): it scales the whole board down so everything is visible at once, sized to your window. It only ever shrinks — a board that already fits is left at full size — and the choice is remembered per dashboard. Dragging and resizing stay accurate while fitted. Pair it with ''Fullscreen'' (the next button) to give the board the entire screen.

!! What does the Fullscreen button do?

It shows //just the dashboard// fullscreen via the browser's Fullscreen API — the whole screen, without the surrounding wiki chrome (sidebar, tabs, browser toolbar). Press it again, or Esc, to exit; the button label and state update either way. In fullscreen the canvas fills the full height beneath the toolbars and scrolls inside itself, so the board uses the whole screen rather than leaving empty space below. It is most useful together with ''Fit to screen'': fullscreen maximises the available area, and fit then scales the board to fill it, so you see everything at once. (Fullscreen requires the click as a user gesture — it can't be triggered programmatically.)

!! A tile shows nothing / only raw text — why?

A tile transcludes the target tiddler's body. Tiddlers whose visible display comes from ViewTemplate //segments// rather than their body — and stream-typed tiddlers, whose `text` field is empty — render thin in a tile. Point the tile at a tiddler with body content, or use a transclusion-bearing wrapper as the target.

!! An image tile shows the full-size image — can it show the thumbnail?

It does by default: if the target was uploaded via [[rimir/file-upload|$:/plugins/rimir/file-upload]] and has a `_thumbnail_uri`, the tile shows that thumbnail (scaled to the tile) rather than the full-size original — so image and PDF tiles stay light. If you want the full image in a tile, open its ⋮ menu → //Show// → ''body'' (or add a display rule mapping those targets to `_canonical_uri`). A target with no thumbnail simply shows its full body as before.

!! What is the difference between the ⧉ popup and clicking a tile to open it?

Clicking a tile ''navigates'' to the target in the story river (leaving the dashboard view). The ⧉ //show contents// control instead opens the target in a centered popup ''on top of'' the dashboard, rendered through the default ViewTemplate — so you can read the full tiddler (title, tags, fields and body) without losing your place. Close it with × or by clicking the backdrop.

!! Can the same tiddler appear on more than one tile?

Yes. A tile is just a tiddler with a `target` field, so nothing stops several tiles — anywhere on the dashboard or across its groups — from pointing at the same target. The quickest way to make one is to hold ''Ctrl'' (or ''Cmd'') while you start dragging a tile: that drops a copy where you release instead of moving the original.

!! How do I put tiles into a group, and nest groups?

Press ''Add group'' for a container tile, then either drop tiddlers from the wiki onto its canvas or drag existing tiles into it. A group's ＋ control adds a group //inside// it, and you can also drag a whole group into another — nesting is recursive with no depth limit. Drag a tile (or group) back onto the root canvas to take it out again. A //collapsed// group is still a drop target: drop a tiddler onto it and the tiddler is added as a child and the group expands (see the collapsed-drop FAQ below).

!! Can a group have an icon?

Yes. Open the group's ⋮ menu and click //Icon…// to open the icon editor: pick a common icon, or enter any tiddler title (such as `$:/core/images/folder`) or inline markup in the input, watch the live preview, and use //Clear// to remove it. (Equivalently, set the group tile's `icon` field directly.) While the group is open the icon shows small before its name. Collapse a group that has an icon and its header becomes //just// the icon: hover it to see the name, click it to expand the group again, or drag the icon to move the group. A collapsed icon is scaled to a configurable box (default 64×64 px, set in the plugin settings) preserving its aspect ratio, so a wide or large image isn't squashed. Groups without an icon keep the usual ▸/▾ toggle and name when collapsed.

!! Can I link a group to a tiddler (give it a "context")?

Yes. A group can be //connected// to a tiddler as its //implicit context// — handy when a group represents "everything about //X//" (a project, a kind entity, a topic). Open the group's ⋮ menu → //Context…// and type a tiddler title (or just drop a tiddler onto the group's header). Linking:

* ''adopts the tiddler's caption'' as the group's name — you can rename the group independently afterwards; the two are not kept in sync;
* shows a ''context chip'' in the header — the tiddler's [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] icon if it is a kind instance, otherwise a link glyph — that ''opens the tiddler in the story river'' when clicked;
* when the context is a kind instance, gives the group the same ✎ //entity// popup a content tile has: //edit// the entity, or //Add child// to create a related instance — with its `parent` pre-set to the context //and its tile dropped inside this group//.

Use //Unlink// in the //Context…// editor (or the ⋮ menu) to disconnect; the current caption is kept.

!! I expanded a group but another tile covers it — how do I keep it on top?

Expanding a group already raises it to the front (its `z` becomes the highest on the dashboard), so its contents sit above the other tiles. If you later move or resize a //different// tile, that tile comes to the front in turn and may overlap the group again — just click the group's ▾/▸ toggle (or move it) to raise it back.

!! What happens to the tiles inside a group when I delete the group?

They are not deleted. Removing a group (its × control) promotes its direct children up to the group's own container — so a group at the top level spills its contents onto the dashboard, and a nested group spills into its parent group. Delete the child tiles individually if you want them gone.

!! Why did my tile snap to a new position when I dragged it into a group?

Positions are relative to the container. When a tile moves into (or out of) a group its coordinates are recomputed relative to the new canvas, so it keeps roughly the on-screen spot where you dropped it rather than its old numbers.

!! Can I collapse a normal (content) tile, not just a group?

Yes — window tiles have a ▸/▾ toggle in their title bar. Collapsing shrinks the tile to just its headline (the caption); if the target has an `icon`, it collapses to just that icon instead — click it to expand, drag it to move, hover for the caption (the same behavior as a collapsed group). Bare tiles have no title bar, so switch a tile to //window// style (the ⊟ action) if you want to collapse it.

!! Can I drop something onto a //collapsed// tile or group?

Yes. A collapsed tile renders no body, but its header still acts as a drop surface — you don't have to expand it first. Drop a tiddler //or// a file onto a collapsed ''group'' and it is added as a child of that group, which then expands so you can see it land. Drop a file onto a collapsed ''content tile'' whose `target` is under `work/` and the file is uploaded into that item's folder (exactly as dropping on the open tile would). There is no permanent drop band — the box is simply outlined while a drag hovers over it. (A collapsed content tile with a non-`work/` target has no attach point, so it doesn't take a drop — the same as when it is expanded; drop on the canvas instead to add it as a new tile.)

!! How do I switch a tile between window and bare?

Use the ⊟ action in the tile's ⋮ menu (the corner cluster revealed on hover). It toggles the tile's `style` field.

!! How do I open a tile's link in a new browser tab?

If the tile's target tiddler has a `url` or `_canonical_uri` field, its ''caption is rendered as a real link'' — hover it to see the address in the browser status bar, click it to open in a new tab. The tile also shows an ↗ button beside its ⋮ menu, and ''Ctrl/Cmd-clicking'' the tile does the same. A plain click elsewhere on the tile still opens the target //inside the wiki//. This is how an uploaded image or file tile (which carries `_canonical_uri`) opens its raw file. The fields consulted and their priority are set in `$:/config/rimir/dashboard/external-open-fields` (default `url _canonical_uri`, first non-empty wins); edit it to add your own field or change the order. Absolute URLs open as-is; a bare host gets `https://` prepended.

!! Can a tile show a tiddler's icon (or some other field) instead of its body?

Yes. By default a tile shows the target's body, but if the target has no (or empty) `text` and an `icon`, the tile shows the icon automatically. To choose explicitly, open the tile's ⋮ menu and pick under //Show//: ''auto'' (the default), ''body'', ''icon'', or type any field name. That sets the tile's `display` field.

To do it for many tiles at once, use ''display rules'' on the dashboard: click //Display rules//, then add a row like `[tag[Image]] ⇒ _canonical_uri` or `[has[icon]] ⇒ icon`. The first rule (by order) whose filter selects a tile's target decides what that tile shows — unless the tile has its own //Show// choice, which always wins. If the chosen field's value points at an image/SVG tiddler it is transcluded; otherwise the field's value is rendered as-is.

!! Clicking a bare tile opens the tiddler instead of interacting with its content — is that expected?

Yes. Bare tiles are previews: their content is non-interactive (`pointer-events: none`) so the whole box reliably acts as move / open surface. Use a window tile when you need to interact with the content.

!! Where is my dashboard's layout stored?

In the tile tiddlers under `$:/config/rimir/dashboard/<dashId>/tiles/…`. They sync to disk like any `$:/config` tiddler. Deleting a dashboard does not delete its tiles automatically — remove them by prefix if you want them gone.

!! Do dashboards nest?

You can point a tile at another dashboard tiddler; it will render that dashboard's canvas inside the tile. Deeply nested dashboards are untested — treat as an edge case.

!! Can a tile show the kind type icon?

Yes — automatically. If a window tile's target is a [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] instance, the type's icon appears before the caption with the type name as hover text. It requires nothing beyond having kind installed and a `kind.icon` on the type; without kind, the icon is simply omitted. (Bare tiles have no title bar, so no icon is shown there.)

!! Can I edit a kind entity, or add children to it, from the dashboard?

Yes, when [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] is installed and the tile's `target` is a kind instance. Hover the ✎ //entity// control next to the tile's ⋮ menu — it opens a compact popup: ''edit'' opens the same live editor modal you get from //Kind: Instances Overview// (change fields, applied immediately), and ''Add child'' shows a button for each kind whose `parent` reference accepts this entity's type — clicking one opens the create modal with `parent` already pointing at this entity, using the same validation and title formula as the Creator. When you create it, a tile for the new child is also dropped onto the dashboard //in the same group as the source tile//, so it shows up right away. The ✎ control is absent on non-entity tiles and when kind isn't installed. (Entity //deletion// is intentionally left to the graph view; the tile's × removes the tile, not the underlying tiddler.)

!! Nothing happens when I drag — the tile just gets selected/dragged as text.

That is a sign the drag region isn't arming (for example an element accidentally marked `.rr-dash-no-drag`). Move starts only on the handle (window) or the box (bare); resize only on the corner grip.

</$fill>
